- Correct: Backend endpoints resolve workspace server-side and scope list/find queries; archive is idempotent and excludes archived products. `dotnet test backend/InventoryFlow.sln --no-restore` passed (29 tests). Frontend production build and lint passed.
- Blocker: **High â cross-tenant product data is exposed through the React Query cache.** `frontend/src/features/products/pages/ProductsPage.tsx:14,29` uses one global `["products"]` key. `frontend/src/lib/query-client.ts:8` keeps it fresh for 30 seconds, while sign-out only clears auth state (`frontend/src/lib/api-client.ts:19-22`; `frontend/src/components/layout/Topbar.tsx:41-48`) and never clears/removes query data. A user who signs out and another user who signs in on the same SPA can receive the previous tenantâs cached product names/SKUs without a request. Scope the key by workspace/user and clear the query cache on session transition.

